<!-- pattern: not-applicable — operator-side activation file mirroring com.minsky.tick-loop.plist; OTP transient-restart semantics already declared at vision.md § "Pattern conformance index" row for the tick-loop plist (Armstrong 2007). -->
<!-- scope: human-approved 2026-05-05 — operator directive: detect stuck iterations and resolve them off-tick. -->
<!--
Minsky watchdog — launchd LaunchAgent for macOS.

Pattern: continuous-watchdog (Beyer SRE 2016 Ch. 6 — every state operator
cares about must surface). Runs `scripts/watchdog.mjs` continuously,
polling self-diagnose invariants and auto-resolving findings whose action
is local + reversible-via-respawn (currently: kill stuck `claude --print`
spawns whose etime exceeds WATCHDOG_STUCK_THRESHOLD_SECONDS).

Source: 2026-05-05 operator dogfood — a daemon iteration ran for 2h+ at
~1% CPU before manual kill. Operator directive: detect + immediately
resolve OUTSIDE supervisor-tick-cadence.

Placeholders substituted by setup.sh via envsubst:
  ${MINSKY_HOME}   — absolute path to the minsky repo checkout

Install: copy to ~/Library/LaunchAgents/ after envsubst, then:
  launchctl bootstrap gui/$(id -u) ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.minsky.watchdog.plist
  launchctl enable gui/$(id -u)/com.minsky.watchdog
-->
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>Label</key>
    <string>com.minsky.watchdog</string>

    <key>WorkingDirectory</key>
    <string>${MINSKY_HOME}</string>

    <key>EnvironmentVariables</key>
    <dict>
        <key>MINSKY_HOME</key>
        <string>${MINSKY_HOME}</string>
        <!-- Tick cadence in seconds. Default 60 (one self-diagnose run per
             minute). Tighten if iterations regress to <30min and threshold
             drops below 1800. -->
        <key>WATCHDOG_INTERVAL_SECONDS</key>
        <string>60</string>
        <!-- Stuck-iteration threshold in seconds. Default 1800 (30 min). The
             observed 2026-05-05 hang was 2h+, so 1800s catches it well within
             one window. Pivot trigger (rule #9): if false-positives >1/week,
             raise to 3600 (1h) before retiring. -->
        <key>WATCHDOG_STUCK_THRESHOLD_SECONDS</key>
        <string>1800</string>
    </dict>

    <key>ProgramArguments</key>
    <array>
        <string>/usr/bin/env</string>
        <string>node</string>
        <string>${MINSKY_HOME}/scripts/watchdog.mjs</string>
    </array>

    <!-- Restart on non-zero exit only (transient policy per Armstrong 2007). -->
    <key>KeepAlive</key>
    <dict>
        <key>SuccessfulExit</key>
        <false/>
    </dict>

    <key>RunAtLoad</key>
    <true/>

    <!-- Backoff between respawn attempts; caps respawn loop on systematic failures. -->
    <key>ThrottleInterval</key>
    <integer>5</integer>

    <key>StandardOutPath</key>
    <string>${MINSKY_HOME}/.minsky/watchdog.out.log</string>
    <key>StandardErrorPath</key>
    <string>${MINSKY_HOME}/.minsky/watchdog.err.log</string>
</dict>
</plist>
